      • testCreatePatientCorrect

        public void testCreatePatientCorrect()
        Tries to create a Patient object using the method BasicDBService.createPatient(String, String). As the Patient object must not be directly stored after creating, this test checks if a Patient object exists in db, yet it should not.
        Involved methods:

      • testStorePatientInsertGetPatient

        public void testStorePatientInsertGetPatient()
        Tries to store and get a Patient object using the BasicDBService.store(PersistentObject) and BasicDBService.getPatient(long) methods. Test succeeds if
        1. storing the Patient object succeeds
        2. the number of all Patient objects in db increases by one
        3. getting the Patient object via its objectID succeeds
        4. the received Patient object matches the given one
        Involved methods:
        • BasicDBService.createPatient(String, String)
        • BasicDBService.getPatients(String, String, Date, Date)

      • testStorePatientUpdateGetPatient

        public void testStorePatientUpdateGetPatient()
        Tries to update and get a Patient object using the BasicDBService.store(PersistentObject) and BasicDBService.getPatient(long) methods. Test succeeds if
        1. storing the Patient object succeeds
        2. updating the Patient object succeeds
        3. the number of all Patient objects in db does not change
        4. getting the Patient object via its objectID succeeds
        5. the received Patient object matches the given one
